*INTRODUCTION*

clever-f.vim extends |f| mapping for more convenience.
You may be able to forget the existence of |;|.
clever-f.vim is distributed under MIT license.
See doc/clever_f.txt to get more information.



*USAGE*

I'll show an example of usage. _ is the place of cursor, -> is a move of
cursor, alphabets above -> is input by keyboard.

input:       fh              f           e         fo         f
move :  _---------->_------------------>_->_---------------->_->_
text :  hoge        huga                hugu                ponyo
